<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">FAQs About Centralized Exchanges</span></h2>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">How do these platforms make money? </span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you are wondering what is CEX revenue modeling, it is quite simple. These platforms primarily generate massive profits by charging transaction trading fees, fiat withdrawal fees, and listing fees for new cryptos. They also make money on the spread between the buy and sell prices in their active order books.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Are they legally regulated? </span></h3>
